About Me
I’m Pritam Karmakar Rony, a Civil & Environmental Engineer and Researcher specializing in water quality & resource modeling. Currently pursuing my MS at Texas A&M University–Kingsville with expertise in HEC‑RAS, Delft3D, GIS, and ML.
Current Work
Click to expand project details
I am currently conducting a research project that focuses on understanding the seasonal and spatial variations in water and sediment quality in the Nueces/Corpus Christi Bay area, Texas. This coastal region, vital for biodiversity, fisheries, and recreation, is increasingly impacted by urban runoff, industrial activity, and climate-induced changes in hydrology. The project involves sampling water and sediment from five key sites — including Labonte Park, Nueces Bay, Sgt. J.D. Bock Park, Sugar Tree Apartments, and Ennis Joslin Road — during both wet and dry seasons.

Measured Parameters:
• Water: pH, DO, salinity, nutrients, heavy metals
• Sediment: grain size, organic content, phosphorus

Findings highlight shifts in salinity, nutrient cycling, and sediment types. Results are being prepared for peer-reviewed publication and presented at the 2025 UCOWR Annual Conference.
